          <bpmn:endEvent id="Event_0zmk9dw">
            <bpmn:incoming>Flow_0aa81tb</bpmn:incoming>
          </bpmn:endEvent>
          <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_0aa81tb" sourceRef="Activity_14gr8p0" targetRef="Event_0zmk9dw" />
          <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_0wgelbu">
            <bpmn:text>Control TP-1: Third-Party Provider Responsibilities

Best Practices:
• Develop AI-specific vendor requirements (see Appendix J.1)
• Create third-party AI risk assessment frameworks (see Appendix J.2)
• Standardize AI service contracts (see Appendix J.3)
Evidence:
• Contractual agreements referencing AI obligations
• Service level agreements (SLAs)
• Responsibility matrices
Roles &amp; Responsibilities:
• Owner: CHFS Procurement/Vendor Risk Management
• Responsible: AI Risk Analyst (for vendor solutions)
• Accountable: Chief Compliance Officer
• Consulted: CHFS AI Governance Team, IT Security
• Informed: Business Units, AI Teams
Frequency:
• Quarterly provider reviews
• Annual obligation assessments
Policy Linkages:
• CHFS Policy 070.110 (Technology Acquisition)
• CHFS Policy 080.101 (Vendor References)
Compliance Requirements:
• GDPR (data processing agreements)
• NIST SP 800-161 (supply chain risk management)
• NIST AI RMF: GOVERN-6, MANAGE-4
• ISO 42001: Clause 9.2 (Third-Party Risk Management)
• EU AI Act: Article 28 (Obligations of Providers and Users), Article 29 (Third-Party Assessment)</bpmn:text>
          </bpmn:textAnnotation>
          <bpmn:association id="Association_0sevrxd" associationDirection="None" sourceRef="Activity_14gr8p0" targetRef="TextAnnotation_0wgelbu" />
        </bpmn:subProcess>
        <bpmn:subProcess id="Activity_14v1iz7" name="Control: TP-2">
          <bpmn:incoming>Flow_006sfit</bpmn:incoming>
          <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_02a16rw</bpmn:outgoing>
          <bpmn:startEvent id="Event_0lgueyb">
            <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_05hywyc</bpmn:outgoing>
          </bpmn:startEvent>
          <bpmn:task id="Activity_00jqx6r" name="Supplier Risk Management">
            <bpmn:incoming>Flow_05hywyc</bpmn:incoming>
            <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_0i9btxe</bpmn:outgoing>
          </bpmn:task>
          <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_05hywyc" sourceRef="Event_0lgueyb" targetRef="Activity_00jqx6r" />
          <bpmn:endEvent id="Event_06d8oly">
            <bpmn:incoming>Flow_0i9btxe</bpmn:incoming>
          </bpmn:endEvent>
          <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_0i9btxe" sourceRef="Activity_00jqx6r" targetRef="Event_06d8oly" />
          <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_1oks35n">
            <bpmn:text>Best Practices:
• Implement supply chain transparency requirements (see Appendix J.4)
• Develop model provenance tracking (see Appendix J.5)
• Establish third-party AI evaluation frameworks (see Appendix J.6)
Evidence:
• Supplier risk assessment reports
• Monitoring procedure records
• Contingency planning documents
• Supply chain security assessments
Roles &amp; Responsibilities:
• Owner: CHFS Procurement/Vendor Risk Management
• Responsible: AI Risk Analyst
• Accountable: Chief Compliance Officer
• Consulted: CHFS IT, CHFS Legal
• Informed: Business Units, AI Teams
Frequency:
• Quarterly risk assessments
• Continuous monitoring
Policy Linkages:
• CHFS Policy 080.101 (Section 4.3 risk management references)
• CHFS Supplier Management Policy
Compliance Requirements:
• ISO 27001 (supplier risk management)
• NIST SP 800-161 (supply chain security)
• NIST AI RMF: GOVERN-6, MEASURE-5
• ISO 42001: Clause 9.2 (Third-Party Risk Management)
• EU AI Act: Article 28 (Obligations of Providers and Users), Annex VIII (Supplier Management Requirements)</bpmn:text>
          </bpmn:textAnnotation>
          <bpmn:association id="Association_0io2nkv" associationDirection="None" sourceRef="Activity_00jqx6r" targetRef="TextAnnotation_1oks35n" />
